[{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_1","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":1,"text":"How will the gold be tarnished, the fine silver changed! the sacred stones have been poured forth at the top of all the streets.","searchKeywords":["how","will","the","gold","tarnished","fine","silver","changed","sacred","stones","have","been","poured","forth","top","all","streets"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_2","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":2,"text":"The precious sons of Zion, who were equalled in value with gold, how are they counted as earthen vessels, the works of the hands of the potter!","searchKeywords":["the","precious","sons","zion","who","were","equalled","value","with","gold","how","are","they","counted","earthen","vessels","works","hands","potter"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_3","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":3,"text":"Nay, serpents have drawn out the breasts, they give suck to their young, the daughters of my people are incurably cruel, as an ostrich in a desert.","searchKeywords":["nay","serpents","have","drawn","out","the","breasts","they","give","suck","their","young","daughters","people","are","incurably","cruel","ostrich","desert"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_4","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":4,"text":"The tongue of the sucking child cleaves to the roof of its mouth for thirst: the little children ask for bread, there is none to break to them.","searchKeywords":["the","tongue","sucking","child","cleaves","roof","its","mouth","for","thirst","little","children","ask","bread","there","none","break","them"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_5","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":5,"text":"They that feed on dainties are desolate in the streets: they that used to be nursed in scarlet have clothed themselves with dung.","searchKeywords":["they","that","feed","dainties","are","desolate","the","streets","used","nursed","scarlet","have","clothed","themselves","with","dung"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_6","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":6,"text":"And the iniquity of the daughter of my people has been increased beyond the iniquities of Sodoma, that was overthrown very suddenly, and none laboured against her hands.","searchKeywords":["and","the","iniquity","daughter","people","has","been","increased","beyond","iniquities","sodoma","that","was","overthrown","very","suddenly","none","laboured","against","her","hands"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_7","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":7,"text":"Her Nazarites were made purer than snow, they were whiter than milk, they were purified with fire, their polishing was superior to sapphire stone.","searchKeywords":["her","nazarites","were","made","purer","than","snow","they","whiter","milk","purified","with","fire","their","polishing","was","superior","sapphire","stone"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_8","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":8,"text":"Their countenance is become blacker than smoke; they are not known in the streets: their skin has cleaved to their bones; they are withered, they are become as a stick.","searchKeywords":["their","countenance","become","blacker","than","smoke","they","are","not","known","the","streets","skin","has","cleaved","bones","withered","stick"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_9","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":9,"text":"The slain with the sword were better than they that were slain with hunger: they have departed, pierced through from the fruits of the field.","searchKeywords":["the","slain","with","sword","were","better","than","they","that","hunger","have","departed","pierced","through","from","fruits","field"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_10","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":10,"text":"The hands of tender-hearted women have sodden their own children: they became meat for them in the destruction of the daughter of my people.","searchKeywords":["the","hands","tender","hearted","women","have","sodden","their","own","children","they","became","meat","for","them","destruction","daughter","people"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_11","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":11,"text":"The Lord has accomplished his wrath; he has poured out his fierce anger, and has kindled a fire in Sion, and it has devoured her foundations.","searchKeywords":["the","lord","has","accomplished","his","wrath","poured","out","fierce","anger","and","kindled","fire","sion","devoured","her","foundations"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_12","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":12,"text":"The kings of the earth, all that dwell in the world, believed not that an enemy and oppressor would enter through the gates of Jerusalem.","searchKeywords":["the","kings","earth","all","that","dwell","world","believed","not","enemy","and","oppressor","would","enter","through","gates","jerusalem"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_13","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":13,"text":"For the sins of her prophets, iniquities of her priests, who shed righteous blood in the midst of her,","searchKeywords":["for","the","sins","her","prophets","iniquities","priests","who","shed","righteous","blood","midst"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_14","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":14,"text":"her watchmen staggered in the streets, they were defiled with blood in their weakness, they touched their raiment .","searchKeywords":["her","watchmen","staggered","the","streets","they","were","defiled","with","blood","their","weakness","touched","raiment"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_15","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":15,"text":"Depart ye from the unclean ones: call ye them: depart, depart, touch not: for they are on fire, yea, they stagger: say ye among the nations, They shall no more sojourn .","searchKeywords":["depart","from","the","unclean","ones","call","them","touch","not","for","they","are","fire","yea","stagger","say","among","nations","shall","more","sojourn"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_16","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":16,"text":"The presence of the Lord their portion; he will not again look upon them: they regarded not the person of the priests, they pitied not the prophets.","searchKeywords":["the","presence","lord","their","portion","will","not","again","look","upon","them","they","regarded","person","priests","pitied","prophets"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_17","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":17,"text":"While we yet lived our eyes failed, while we looked in vain for our help. We looked to a nation that could not save.","searchKeywords":["while","yet","lived","our","eyes","failed","looked","vain","for","help","nation","that","could","not","save"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_18","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":18,"text":"We have hunted our little ones, that they should not walk in our streets. Our time has drawn nigh, our days are fulfilled, our time is come.","searchKeywords":["have","hunted","our","little","ones","that","they","should","not","walk","streets","time","has","drawn","nigh","days","are","fulfilled","come"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_19","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":19,"text":"Our pursuers were swifter than the eagles of the sky, they flew on the mountains, in the wilderness they laid wait for us.","searchKeywords":["our","pursuers","were","swifter","than","the","eagles","sky","they","flew","mountains","wilderness","laid","wait","for"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_20","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":20,"text":"The breath of our nostrils, anointed Lord, was taken in their destructive snares, of whom we said, In his shadow we shall live among the Gentiles.","searchKeywords":["the","breath","our","nostrils","anointed","lord","was","taken","their","destructive","snares","whom","said","his","shadow","shall","live","among","gentiles"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_21","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":21,"text":"Rejoice and be glad, O daughter of Idumea, that dwellest in the land: yet the cup of the Lord shall pass through to thee: thou shalt be drunken, and pour forth.","searchKeywords":["rejoice","and","glad","daughter","idumea","that","dwellest","the","land","yet","cup","lord","shall","pass","through","thee","thou","shalt","drunken","pour","forth"]},{"verseId":"brenton_lamentations_4_22","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":48,"bookName":"Lamentations","bookAbbrev":"lamentations","chapter":4,"verse":22,"text":"O daughter of Sion, thine iniquity has come to an end; he shall no more carry thee captive: he has visited thine iniquities, O daughter of Edom; he has discovered thy sins.","searchKeywords":["daughter","sion","thine","iniquity","has","come","end","shall","more","carry","thee","captive","visited","iniquities","edom","discovered","thy","sins"]}]